narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Good class--lots of fun books/movies. And good professor.
I would definitely recommend this class. Take it with Koundi, she is great.
It's a French class at Yale. It's a lot of work, but it will definitely improve your language skills - both grammatically and orally.

Good class, a lot of busy work though. It's not hard to do well in the class though as long as you do all of your work - the amount of work is an excellent reinforcement and really hammers the concepts into your brain.
I would recommend this course if you are looking to improve your grammar.
Yes I definitely would. It has brought my friends on leaps and bounds.

Take it if you would like to review your grammar. Speaking is emphasized but you'll find that it is a lot of work. Make sure you do the work because it will improve your fluency, even though it's a pain.
I would recommend it. It helps you improve both your grammar and oral communication while you read works in french.
